                  </hi>. I am the wife of James Bacon, and live at Mrs. Edwards's. On the 9th of August, I was looking out of window, and saw the prisoner carrying a bag and matches—he asked if I wanted any—I noticed that a garden pot was moved from the window—I went down and spoke to Mrs. Edwards—I then ran out and found the prisoner walking down the lane—he threw the blanket out of his bag on seeing me, and I took it up.</p>
